# UI layer boundaries

Canonical write-up: **`docs/coding-guidebook.md`** §2–3.

## Dependency direction

```text
page.tsx → feature (src/app/**/components) → shell (src/components) → primitives (src/ui) → theme
```

Never import upward. Primitives must not import app routes, Apollo, or Me store.

## `src/ui` — universal primitives only

- Atoms/molecules reusable on **any** route (Button, Input, Card, Avatar, Drawer, …).
- Presentational: **no** Apollo hooks, **no** `useUserStore`, **no** pathname branching for chrome.
- No marketplace-scoped defaults (e.g. EmptyState with hardcoded quotes art). Compose `SpotIllustration` + local Stack in features.
- No domain status enums (`TaskStatusValue` / `StatusPill`) — feature adapters compose `Badge`.
- Extend existing primitives with optional props before adding forks.
- Avatar load fallbacks: `srcCandidates` + `fallback: 'initials' | 'icon'`. App adapters (e.g. `MeAvatar`) resolve Me/Google URLs outside `src/ui`.

## `src/components` — app shell chrome

- Cross-route, app-aware chrome: **`Header`**, **`Dock`** (and their menus/drawers).
- May read Me / notifications / routes.
- Import as `@/components/Header`, `@/components/Dock`.
- Stories: `shell/Header`, `shell/Dock` — not `ui/*`.

## `src/app` — features

- Route sections, mappers (`helpers/`), providers (`context/`), GraphQL.
- Thin adapters that wire store/context into `@ui` (no new primitive unless domain-agnostic and multi-caller).
- Domain cards stay presentational; one entity + view/state — no per-route card forks.

## Checklist

- [ ] New shared control → `src/ui` with `ui/<Name>` story, or extend an existing primitive.
- [ ] App-only chrome → `src/components`, not `src/ui`.
- [ ] Route UI → colocated `components/` next to `page.tsx`.
- [ ] No `@/app` imports from `src/ui/**`.
